DEFECT REPORTS

Please send bug reports software@cello.hpl.hp.com.  Please note that
we cannot help you debug your installation, software setup, or
C++ knowledge.

In return, we would greatly appreciate any bug fixes or enhancements -
or even simply hearing about how you are using the package.

BUILDING

1) If you have a copy of Lintel checked out from version control, then
   you need to run autoreconf --install in the source directory.  You
   will need to have already installed autoconf and libtool.

2) configure the package, e.g. in ~/build/optimize/Lintel:
   .../path/to/source/Lintel/configure --enable-optmode=optimize

3) compile and install the package, e.g. in ~/build/optimize/Lintel:
   make && make check && make install

For more details, see doc/building.html

